    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Available is a well-maintained E92 M3 featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio to produce 414 hp at a 8,300 RPM redline. The drivetrain consists of a 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch transmission and a variable M differential lock for superior longitudinal and lateral dynamics. Preventative maintenance is up to date, including addressed rod bearings and throttle actuators. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC), providing adjustable compression and rebound settings. The exterior shows minor stone chipping on the front fascia, but the subframe and suspension bushings remain within factory tolerances. A mechanically robust example of the final naturally aspirated M-car.",
